<%- include('partials/head') %>

    <%- include('partials/navbar') %>

        <main>

            <!-- HERO SECTION -->
            <section class="hero">
                <h1 class="hero-title">because<br>fashion is truly<br>about you</h1>
            </section>


            <!-- INFO SECTION -->
            <section class="info">

                <!-- first content wrapper -->
                <div class="info-row">
                    <div class="info-image">
                        <img src="/images/pinterest_vogueFashionTrend.jpeg" alt="A long line of models walking in formation down a runway at a fashion show, shot from above, with a seated audience watching from the side. Black and white photography">
                    </div>

                    <div class="info-textbox info-textbox--black">
                        <div class="info-text">
                            <p>Fashion has always known what it wants to say. The question is who gets to say it. For a long time, the answer has been the same: insiders, editors, people who were invited. Everyone else watches, scrolls, and keeps their opinion to themselves. Meanwhile, algorithms decide what gets seen, and microtrends cycle faster than personal style can form. And the opinions that do make it through are rarely more than a verdict. This is ugly. That is over. No reason given. No argument made. Just exclusion, dressed up as taste.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-title">
                            <h3>the scene.</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- second content wrapper -->
                <div class="info-row">
                    <div class="info-textbox info-textbox--red">
                        <div class="info-text">
                           <p>A cold take is not the fast one. It is not the reaction that chases the moment or the statement that needs an audience to feel true. It is the opinion you held before it was popular to hold it. Considered, unhurried, independent of the trend cycle. Coldtake exists for that kind of thought. Not the verdict, but the argument behind it. Not the loudest voice, but the most honest one. A place where fashion opinions are given the space they deserve. Reasoned, written out, and entirely your own.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-title">
                            <h3>your role.</h3>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="info-image">
                        <img src="/images/pinterest_individualityFashion.jpeg" alt="A young man stands still on a busy pedestrian crossing, holding a skateboard, while the crowd around him blurs in motion. Black and white photography">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>


            <!-- MOST VIEWD TAKES SECTION -->
            <section class="popular-takes">
                <h2 class="page-title">popular takes.</h2>

                <div class="slider">
                    <!-- visible Article Window -->
                    <div class="slider-track">
                        <!-- Article Card-->
                        <% article.forEach(article => { %>
                            <a href="/takes/<%= article.slug %>" class="article-card slider-article-card">
                                <div class="article-card-image">
                                    <% if (article.coverImageUrl) { %>
                                        <img src="<%= article.coverImageUrl %>" alt="<%= article.title %>">
                                    <% } %>
                                </div>
                                <div class="article-card-info">
                                    <span class="article-card-info-author"> <%= article.authorName %></span>
                                    <h3 class="article-card-info-title"><%= article.title %></h3>
                                </div>
                            </a>
                        <% })  %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>


            <!-- CONTACT US SECTION -->
            <!-- contact form temporarily disabled: future feat. add
